sequenceDiagram
    participant A as Admin
    participant F as React Frontend
    participant API as Node.js Backend
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    Note over A,DB: Admin Dashboard Operations

    %% Login
    A->>F: Enters admin credentials
    F->>API: POST /api/auth/login
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM users WHERE email='admin@3akarati.com'
    DB-->>API: User with role='admin'
    API->>API: Create session, set cookie
    API-->>F: 200 {role: "admin"}
    F-->>A: Redirects to Admin Dashboard

    %% Dashboard Stats
    F->>API: GET /api/admin/stats
    API->>DB: COUNT users, properties, contacts
    DB-->>API: {total_users, total_properties, ...}
    API-->>F: Dashboard KPIs
    F-->>A: Displays stat cards

    %% User Management
    A->>F: Navigates to Users tab
    F->>API: GET /api/admin/users?page=1
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM users LIMIT 10 OFFSET 0
    DB-->>API: Users array + total count
    API-->>F: Paginated user list
    F-->>A: Displays user table

    %% Role Change
    A->>F: Changes user role to 'seller'
    F->>API: PATCH /api/admin/users/:id/role
    API->>DB: UPDATE users SET role='seller'
    API->>DB: INSERT INTO admin_activity_log
    DB-->>API: Updated user
    API-->>F: 200 {role: "seller"}
    F-->>A: Shows updated role

    %% Property Moderation
    A->>F: Views property details
    F->>API: GET /api/admin/properties/:id
    API->>DB: SELECT property + media + contacts
    DB-->>API: Full property data
    API-->>F: Property details
    F-->>A: Shows property modal

    A->>F: Clicks "Reject" with reason
    F->>API: POST /api/admin/properties/:id/reject
    API->>DB: UPDATE properties SET moderation_status='rejected'
    API->>DB: INSERT INTO admin_activity_log
    DB-->>API: OK
    API-->>F: 200 {message: "rejected"}
    F-->>A: Property marked as rejected

    %% Security Logs
    A->>F: Navigates to Security Logs tab
    F->>API: GET /api/admin/security-logs?page=1
    API->>DB: SELECT * FROM security_logs ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 10 OFFSET 0
    DB-->>API: Security logs array + total count
    API-->>F: Paginated security logs
    F-->>A: Displays security logs table with IP, action, OS, and browser details
